# Communications Rules

## Architecture: Channel Abstraction Layer
All guest communications are routed through a unified service in `lib/communications/`. Business logic never calls SendGrid or Twilio directly.

```typescript
// Correct - use the abstraction
import { sendCommunication } from '@/lib/communications';
await sendCommunication({
  type: 'booking_confirmation',
  recipient: { email: guest.email, phone: guest.phone },
  payload: { guestName, venueName, bookingDate, bookingTime, ... }
});

// WRONG - never do this from business logic
import sgMail from '@sendgrid/mail';
await sgMail.send({ ... }); // ❌
```

The service routes messages to the correct channel (email, SMS) based on message type. WhatsApp will be added as a third provider in Phase 2 without changing business logic.

## Message Types and Channels
| Message Type | Channel | Timing |
|---|---|---|
| booking_confirmation | Email | Immediately on confirmed |
| deposit_payment_request | Email + SMS | Immediately on phone booking |
| deposit_payment_reminder | SMS | 2 hours after unpaid request |
| pre_visit_reminder | Email | 48 hours before reservation |
| confirm_or_cancel_prompt | SMS | 24 hours before reservation |
| dietary_digest | Email (kitchen) | Morning of reservation day |
| post_visit_thankyou | Email | 3 hours after reservation end |
| auto_cancel_notification | Email + SMS | 24h after unpaid deposit |
| booking_modification | Email | Immediately on change |

## Template Variables
All templates support these merge variables:
`{{guest_name}}`, `{{venue_name}}`, `{{booking_date}}`, `{{booking_time}}`, `{{party_size}}`, `{{deposit_amount}}`, `{{cancellation_deadline}}`, `{{venue_address}}`, `{{dietary_notes}}`, `{{occasion}}`, `{{confirm_link}}`, `{{cancel_link}}`, `{{payment_link}}`, `{{manage_booking_link}}`

Templates are stored per venue in the `communication_templates` JSONB field on the venues table. Each venue gets sensible defaults which they can customise.

## Confirm-or-Cancel Prompt
This is the most important communication for no-show reduction.
- Sent via SMS 24 hours before reservation.
- Contains a short link to a web page (not two separate links in the SMS).
- The web page shows booking details and two buttons: "Confirm I'm Coming" and "Cancel My Booking".
- Cancel button leads to a secondary confirmation showing deposit implications.
- **Not responding does NOT cancel the booking.** The booking stands.
- The web page must be mobile-optimised and branded with the venue name.

## SMS Cost Awareness
UK SMS costs ~4–5p per message via Twilio. Keep SMS short and purposeful. Use email for content-rich messages. SMS is for time-sensitive, action-required messages only.

## Communication Logging
Every message sent must be logged in the `communications` table with: message type, channel, recipient, timestamp, delivery status, and template version. This is the audit trail and debugging tool.

## Provider Implementation Pattern
```typescript
// lib/communications/providers/sendgrid.ts
export async function sendEmail(to: string, template: CompiledTemplate): Promise<DeliveryResult> { ... }

// lib/communications/providers/twilio.ts
export async function sendSMS(to: string, body: string): Promise<DeliveryResult> { ... }

// lib/communications/index.ts - the router
export async function sendCommunication(message: CommunicationRequest): Promise<void> {
  const channels = getChannelsForMessageType(message.type);
  const template = compileTemplate(message.type, message.payload);
  for (const channel of channels) {
    const result = await providers[channel].send(message.recipient, template);
    await logCommunication(message, channel, result);
  }
}
```
